The grid items allowed for more in-depth answers but it was not easy to understand right away. I believe surveys using this item would benefit from incorporating some grid 'understanding' questions into their survey. These would be questions that only serve to establish whether or not the user understands how to answer grid items, and would only be known to the researcher. I believe they would help show whether or not the tester answered the questions as the item intended, and it therefore the researcher would not have to worry about the validity of their data in that regard.
